 which can appear =\r\nto help out, directly or indirectly, in any transition. A Vibuti need not b=\r\ne spiritual. It could be in any field of work.=C2=A0Sometimes a Vibhuti may=\r\n not even be aware of its purpose, unlike an Avatara.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Basi=\r\ncally, whenever we see excellence in any form, in any field, it is always t=\r\nhe energy of the One at work..\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;-Regards\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0Rajarsh=\r\ni\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;awaktam wyaktimApannam manyantE mAmabuddhayah |param bhA=\r\nwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||[7:24]\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;From: Narasimha P=\r\n.V.R. Rao &lt;pvr108@...&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;To: &quot;vedic-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&quot; &lt;vedic=\r\n-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&gt; \n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Sent: Sunday, 5 May 2013 6:20 AM\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Subjec=\r\nt: [vedic-wisdom] Re: Comparing Dasavataras!\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0 \n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Namast=\r\ne Rajarshi,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Very nice to hear from you!\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;T=\r\nhe &quot;unmistakeable&quot; link to the *physical* evolution of life on earth does n=\r\not imply an increasing sequence of *spiritual* perfection, as you cannot di=\r\nrectly map the physical to the spiritual. More importantly, if your underst=\r\nanding is correct, why isn&#39;t perfection occurring in the FINAL incarnation =\r\nbut occurring well before?\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=\r\n&gt;First, regarding Krishna being a &quot;poornavatara&quot;, SrimadBhagavatam (SB) doe=\r\ns not say that Rama is not one. In fact, Parasara, father of Vyasa, explici=\r\ntly mentioned tha