amatma (supreme/absolute being) and jiva=\r\ntma (living/relative being). The latter portion is dominant in us and is re=\r\nsponsible for desires and rebirth. Great avataras descend from a higher por=\r\ntion of paramatma. Very rarely avataras descend entirely from paramatma wit=\r\nhout ANY jivatma portion. Rama and Krishna are specific examples given by P=\r\narasara.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;They are entirely divine, but they do not encapsu=\r\nlate the entire divinity!!!! After all, &quot;entire\n divinity&quot; cannot be encaps=\r\nulated by any form just as no cloud can contain the entire sky. They take p=\r\nart in the drama obeying and executing the divine will but NOT altering it.=\r\n This applies to Krishna as well as Rama.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=\r\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; Buddha was great spiritual force in this world. But I do =\r\nnot\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; see him fit in the scheme of evolutionary Avatars. His\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; re=\r\nalization, the one he advocated, is a static realization,\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; an end in =\r\na void.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;First, he IS mentioned in SB list of avataras as w=\r\nell as Parasara&#39;s list. If he does not &quot;fit&quot; in your &quot;scheme of evolutionar=\r\ny Avatars&quot;, then your concept is possibly wrong and avataras are perhaps no=\r\nt &quot;evolutionary&quot; as you theorize.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;Secondly, as per Parasar=\r\na, Buddha corresponds to Mercury, who personifies logical mind and the spir=\r\nit of investigation and comprehension. Logical mind\n and its spirit of comp=\r\nrehension are inherently fallible. Even a perfected spirit of comprehension=\r\n is not capable of grasping the Absolute Reality completely, for it is beyo=\r\nnd comprehension. So, no wonder it simplifies the Incomprehensible in an at=\r\ntempt to comprehend! That is what Buddha ended up doing. However, logical m=\r\nind has a great appeal in the Age of Reason in this Kali yuga. No wonder Bu=\r\nddha was/is/will be a great spiritual force in this world in this age.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=\r\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;If you dismiss Parasara&#39;s li=\r\nnking of planets to avataras as a possible corruption, are you absolutely s=\r\nure that the verses of SB you are relying on are perfect? (In any case, it&#39;=\r\ns a different matter that you are only taking some SB verses and ignoring s=\r\nome as\n I\n showed!.)\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;The bottomline as far as I am concern=\r\ned is that Pararsara&#39;s list actually makes amazingly coherent esoteric sens=\r\ne. The nature of each aspect of consciousness (e.g. Buddha - spirit of comp=\r\nrehension, Saturn - spirit of patience & persistence, Venus - spirit of hap=\r\npiness etc) and the story of corresponding avatara DOES have a highly meani=\r\nngful connection, esoterically speaking. After all, esoterically is how you=\r\n really need to understand any higher scriptures and notions in them.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=\r\n=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;If we take scriptures literally instead and draw lopsided concl=\r\nusions, some would conclude that Shiva is the &quot;supreme&quot; one and other deiti=\r\nes are &quot;inferior&quot;; some would conclude that Surya is the &quot;supreme&quot; one and =\r\nother deities are &quot;inferior&quot;; and so on.\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;=\r\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;On a different note, someone may think that Kali, being Aad=\r\nyaa, i